text:
Checklist of benefits for single pensioners
05 Nov 2019, 07:17 by Svetlana Petropolskaya
Every year, the state is trying to pay more and more attention to pension issues. From time to time, the range of measures to support pensioners is expanding. But, unfortunately, due to age, it is rather difficult for people of advanced age to navigate in dynamically changing legislation. For this reason, most of them have no idea about the benefits and various kinds of preferences to which they have every right.
And it is about the benefits and preferences for single pensioners that will be discussed in today's article.
Who is the lone senior citizen entitled to benefits?
This is a citizen who retired and:

Lives separately from relatives, or does not have them;
Needs financial, social or medical support from the state (the need for support must be documented, for example, a certificate of disability);

Social benefits, which can be issued directly to the social protection authorities
Their list includes: Disable ads

benefits for the purchase of food, clothing and other necessary things;
home care benefits (for example, cleaning the living room);
preferential services for escorting a pensioner to a medical or other public institution.

Medical benefits
The list of benefits of this type depends on the region in which the elderly person lives.
In Moscow, a pensioner can count on:

free medical examination and vaccination;
free prosthetics;
discounts on the purchase of drugs;
receiving a free voucher for treatment in a sanatorium.

Housing benefits
This kind of privilege is associated with compensation for payment of utility bills. In this case, the amount of compensation will depend on the following criteria: Turn off advertising

the amount of family expenses to pay utility bills. Compliance with this condition is not always required;
retired age;
preferential status: participant of the Second World War, liquidator of the accident at the Chernobyl nuclear power plant.

Tax incentives
The Federal Tax Service provides the following benefits to pensioners:

exempts pensions and benefits from personal income tax;
exemption of a pensioner from paying real estate tax on one of the selected real estate objects;
if a pensioner owns a specially equipped car, he is entitled to certain transport tax benefits;
13% tax deduction when buying a new property;
discount on land tax. The size of such a discount is from 50 to 100%. This benefit, as well as specific conditions and the procedure for its provision, are established by regional authorities.


In addition to the above benefits, pensioners may be provided with:


free use of public transport;
payment / compensation for mobile communications;
payment / compensation for garbage collection services.




